# Linting Discipline

- Run linting after meaningful code changes.
- For files touched in the current task, lint those files with zero warnings allowed.
- Before finishing, run project-wide linting and ensure there are no errors in the full codebase.
- If lint output reports issues introduced by the current task, fix them before finishing.
- Do not suppress rules to make checks pass unless there is a documented, justified exception.

## Command Guidance

```bash
# Touched files: no warnings allowed
npm run lint -- --max-warnings 0 <changed-file-1> <changed-file-2>

# Full project: no lint errors
npm run lint

# Always run prettier format
npm run format
```
